y%20wasn't%20a%20formalized%20branch%20of%20scientific%20research%2C%20but%20the%20race%20to%20find%20the%20origin%20of%20this%20disease%20laid%20the%20groundwork%20for%20its%20creation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20British%20physician%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F6359513%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EJohn%20Vetch%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20realized%20the%20pus%20from%20the%20infected%20eye%20could%20spread%20the%20disease.%20Knowing%20it%20was%20contagious%2C%20Vetch%20developed%20methods%20of%20prevention%20and%20treatment%20that%20are%20considered%20milestones%20in%20the%20history%20of%20ophthalmology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E6.%20The%20Rosetta%20Stone%20helped%20Champollion%20discover%20how%20to%20decipher%20hieroglyphs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20centuries%2C%20no%20one%20could%20read%20hieroglyphs%2C%20the%20pictorial%20writing%20that%20covered%20many%20Egyptian%20monuments.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisputed-ancient-artifacts-2011-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFrench%20found%20the%20Rosetta%20Stone%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20their%20invasion%2C%20they%20knew%20it%20could%20serve%20as%20a%20kind%20of%20translation%20key.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeciphering%20hieroglyphs%20would%20allow%20scholars%20to%20read%20the%20writing%20on%20scores%20of%20other%20Ancient%20Egyptian%20texts%20and%20monuments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201801%2C%20the%20British%20were%20negotiating%20for%20France's%20surrender.%20One%20stipulation%20was%20that%20the%20British%20would%20take%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.archaeology.org%2F9905%2Fabstracts%2Fegypt.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eantiquities%20and%20the%20savants'%20collections%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20included%20the%20Rosetta%20Stone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeoffroy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fbooks%2Fedition%2FMirage%2Fn--z6iyUooUC%3Fhl%3Den%26gbpv%3D1%26dq%3Dmirage%2Bnapoleon%2527s%2Bscientists%2Band%2Bthe%2Bunveiling%2Bof%2Begypt%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20the%20British%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20savants%20would%20%26quot%3Bdestroy%20our%20property%2C%20we%20will%20disperse%20it%20in%20the%20Libyan%20sands%2C%20or%20we%20will%20throw%20it%20into%20the%20sea%26quot%3B%20before%20they%20handed%20it%20over.%20They%20were%20allowed%20to%20keep%20their%20notes%20and%20collections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221914%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20and%20woman%20in%201930s%20clothing%20stand%20in%20front%20of%20and%20behind%20the%20Rosetta%20Stone%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65693d0b86933e8fdb2eab3a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Rosetta%20Stone%20is%20housed%20at%20the%20British%20Museum.%3Cp%3EFox%20Photos%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20texts%20were%20inscribed%20on%20the%20stone%2C%20in%20Egyptian%20hieroglyphs%2C%20an%20Egyptian%20cursive%20script%20derived%20from%20hieroglyphs%2C%20and%20Ancient%20Greek.%20Since%20the%20three%20were%20identical%2C%20the%20Greek%20writing%20could%20help%20researchers%20decipher%20the%20hieroglyphs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20two%20decades%20for%20French%20scholar%20Jean-Fran%C3%A7ois%20Champollion%20to%20translate%20them.%20Champollion%20made%20use%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnapoleon.lindahall.org%2Frosetta_stone.shtml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecopy%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20French%20savants%20had%20taken%20of%20the%20slab%20and%20published.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Rosetta%20Stone%20is%20currently%20in%20the%20British%20Museum.%20Egypt%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20get%20it%20back%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bspoil%20of%20war.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E7.%20The%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Einvention%20of%20an%20engraving%20machine%20that%20sped%20up%20the%20printing%20process%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20savants%20returned%20to%20France%2C%20many%20worked%20on%20compiling%20the%20multi-volume%20book%20%26quot%3BDescription%20de%20l'E%CC%81gypte%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20amounted%20to%207%2C000%20pages%20encompassing%20what%20they'd%20seen%20and%20studied%20in%20Egypt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20save%20some%20of%20the%20laborious%20work%20of%20engraving%2C%20engineer%20Nicolas-Jacques%20Cont%C3%A9%20created%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnapoleon.lindahall.org%2Fengraving.shtml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emachine%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20automated%20part%20of%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20print%20the%20hundreds%20of%20illustrations%2C%20engravers%20first%20had%20to%20transfer%20them%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.archaeology.org%2F9905%2Fabstracts%2Fegypt.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecopper%20plates%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222115%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20drawing%20of%20a%20domed%20mosque%20and%20tall%20tower%20in%20Cairo%20circa%201798%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65693ed947f9ecb37d88f3ed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJust%20one%20of%20the%20many%20detailed%20engravings%20added%20to%20the%20Description%20de%20l'Egypte%2C%20this%20one%20of%20a%20mosque%20in%20Cairo.%3Cp%3EScience%20%26amp%3B%20Society%20Picture%20Library%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20plates%20with%20monuments%2C%20Cont%C3%A9's%20machine%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.archaeology.org%2F9905%2Fabstracts%2Fegypt.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eengrave%20the%20sky%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20background.%20The%20engraver%20could%20program%20it%20to%20create%20clouds%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20originally%20would've%20taken%20six%20to%20eight%20months%20could%20be%20completed%20in%20just%20a%20few%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20still%20a%20massive%20undertaking%20and%20considered%20to%20be%20the%20most%20ambitious%20work%20of%20France%20in%20the%20early%2019th%20Century.%20The%20first%20volume%20wasn't%20printed%20until%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Foaj%2Farticle%2F39%2F2%2F243%2F2223028%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E1809%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20final%20volume%20came%20out%20in%20the%20late%201820s%2C%20nearly%20a%20decade%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ngv.vic.gov.au%2Fnapoleon%2Fnapoleon-and-josephine%2Fwho-was-napoleon.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENapoloen's%20death%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnapoleon-egypt-invasion-scientific-breakthroughs-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701513421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6569306286933e8fdb2eaa5c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnapoleon-egypt-invasion-scientific-breakthroughs-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Over%20150%20scientists%20went%20with%20Napoleon%20Bonaparte%20when%20he%20invaded%20Egypt.%20They%20mapped%20pyramids%2C%20dissected%20mummies%2C%20and%20did%20more%20scientific%20work.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jmcgrath%40insider.com%20(Jenny%20McGrath)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnapoleon-egypt-invasion-scientific-breakthroughs-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22World's%20'saddest'%20elephant%20dies%20after%20more%20than%2040%20years%20alone%20in%20a%20concrete%20pen%20at%20Manila%20Zoo%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Visitors%20watch%20a%2038-year-old%20elephant%20named%20%26quot%3BMali%26quot%3B%20inside%20an%20enclosure%20at%20Manila