0Thursday%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20isn't%20available%20in%20Europe%2C%20despite%20the%20European%20Union%20being%20both%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-germany-berlin-gigafactory-ships-cars-265-day-delay-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ean%20important%20manufacturing%20hub%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20key%20market%20for%20Tesla.%20There%20are%20a%20few%20reasons%20why%20it's%20unlikely%20to%20be%20sold%20across%20the%20Atlantic%20anytime%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20is%20simple%3A%20the%20Cybertruck%20is%20extremely%20heavy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvpic.nhtsa.dot.gov%2Fmid%2Fhome%2Fdisplayfile%2Ffbec7f77-5e2b-4d06-b46c-267e7327c2ff%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EDocuments%20submitted%20to%20US%20regulators%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20show%20that%20the%20minimum%20gross%20vehicle%20weight%20range%20is%208%2C001%20to%209%2C001%20pounds%2C%20or%204%20to%204.5%20tons%2C%20which%20could%20prove%20an%20issue%20if%20Tesla%20wanted%20to%20sell%20the%20pickup%20in%20Europe%20as%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20vehicle's%20gross%20vehicle%20weight%20for%20the%20dual-motor%20version%20is%20high%2C%20above%203.5%20tons%2C%26quot%3B%20Pedro%20Pacheco%2C%20vice-president%20of%20research%20at%20Gartner%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20has%20implications%20for%20European%20regulations%2C%20because%20it%20means%20that%2C%20most%20likely%2C%20a%20passenger%20vehicle%20driver's%20license%20will%20not%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWeight%20worries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20drive%20a%20vehicle%20heavier%20than%203.5%20tons%20in%20the%20EU%2C%20drivers%20must%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feuropeanlorrydriving.co.uk%2Fbecome-a-european-hgv-driver%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20category%20C1%20license%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20that%20to%20drive%20a%20US-built%20Cybertruck%20on%20European%20roads%2C%20you%20may%20need%20to%20apply%20for%20a%20truck%20driver's%20license.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20obstacle%20is%20that%20the%20Cybertruck's%20charging%20port%20isn't%20compatible%20with%20European%20chargers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Cybertrucks%20rolling%20off%20Tesla%20production%20lines%20in%20the%20US%20work%20with%20the%20Tesla%20NAC%20standard%2C%20which%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-charge-non-tesla-ev-at-supercharger-models-adapters-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewidely%20adopted%20across%20the%20US%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20not%20with%20the%20CCS%20network%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rac.co.uk%2Fdrive%2Felectric-cars%2Fcharging%2Fcharging-your-electric-vehicle-in-europe%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eused%20by%20most%20European%20nations%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPacheco%20added%20that%20Tesla%20would%20probably%20seek%20to%20make%20adjustments%20to%20ensure%20that%20an%20EU%20Cybertruck%20could%20drive%20on%20European%20roads%2C%20including%20making%20their%20charging%20tech%20compatible%20with%20CCS%20and%20reducing%20weight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bigger%20question%20is%20whether%20Tesla%20can%20be%20bothered%20making%20these%20tweaks%2C%20considering%20the%20relative%20unpopularity%20of%20hulking%20pickups%20like%20the%20Cybertruck%20in%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPickup%20trucks%20are%20somewhat%20small%20in%20terms%20of%20market%20adoption%20in%20comparison%20to%20what%20you%20see%20in%20the%20US%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Pacheco.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20a%20vehicle%20in%20the%20category%20of%20the%20Cybertruck%2C%20there's%20not%20a%20huge%20market%20in%20Europe%2C%20because%20pickup%20trucks%20generally%20are%20not%20very%20common.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20European%20market%20for%20pickups%20is%20mostly%20focused%20on%20what%20Pacheco%20calls%20%26quot%3Bentry-l