al%2Fdespite-early-gains-of-swachh-bharat-mission-toilet-use-declining-since-2018-19-world-bank-paper%2Farticle67376731.ece%5C%22%3Ebreathtaking%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20gains%20in%20increasing%20toilet%20access%2C%20toilet%20usage%20had%20been%20going%20down%20in%20rural%20India%20since%202018.%20The%20largest%20drop%20in%20usage%20is%20reported%20among%20people%20from%20Scheduled%20Caste%20(20%20percentage%20points)%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribe%20(24%20percentage%20points)%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20findings%20fly%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20claims%20that%20practices%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fdespite-early-gains-of-swachh-bharat-mission-toilet-use-declining-since-2018-19-world-bank-paper%2Farticle67376731.ece%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3Eopen%20defecation%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20manual%20scavenging%20no%20longer%20exist%20in%20India%2C%20based%20on%20the%20fact%20that%20toilet%20access%20had%20improved%20after%20the%20building%20of%20over%20100%20million%20toilets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20government%20spokesperson%2C%20whom%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reached%20out%20to%2C%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20matter%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpurely%20World%20Bank%20issue%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20under%20scanner%20was%20churned%20out%20based%20on%20the%20data%20points%20on%20toilet%20access%20and%20usage%20from%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20National%20Family%20Health%20Surveys%2C%20National%20Sample%20Surveys%2C%20the%20National%20Annual%20Rural%20Sanitation%20Survey%20(NARSS)%2C%20and%20the%20Swachch%20Bharat%20Mission-Grameen%E2%80%99s%20information%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NARSS%2C%20conducted%20across%20rural%20India%20from%202017-18%20to%202019-20%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Drinking%20Water%20and%20Sanitation%20with%20World%20Bank%20support%2C%20showed%20that%20as%20the%20SBM-G%20began%2C%20it%20led%20to%20a%20substantial%20increase%20in%20access%20to%20own%20or%20shared%20improved%20toilets%20in%20rural%20India.%20It%20rose%20from%2038%25%20in%202012%20to%2090%25%20in%202019-20%2C%20and%20the%20last%20two%20years%20during%20this%20period%20saw%20the%20fastest%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAt%20the%20national%20level%2C%20regular%20use%20of%20any%20toilet%20%5Bimproved%20or%20unimproved%5D%20increased%20from%2046%25%20to%2075%25%20on%20average%20in%20rural%20areas%20during%202015-16%20and%202019-21.%20This%20increase%20was%20across%20all%20population%20and%20socio-economic%20sub-groups%20we%20track%2C%20and%20especially%20pronounced%20for%20the%20poor%20and%20socially%20disadvantaged%20groups%2C%E2%80%9D%20concluded%20the%20now-withdrawn%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20had%20been%20reversals.%20Even%20as%20the%20regular%20use%20of%20any%20toilet%20for%20SC%20(51%20percentage%20points)%20and%20ST%20(58%20percentage%20points)%20people%20saw%20a%20jump%20between%202015-16%20and%202018-19%2C%20which%20is%20almost%20the%20same%20level%20as%20those%20in%20the%20General%20Category%2C%20the%20paper%20said%20these%20gains%20had%20begun%20to%20reverse%20since%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20from%202018%2C%20there%20had%20been%20a%2020%20percentage%20point%20decline%20in%20regular%20use%20of%20toilets%20for%20the%20SC%20population%20and%20a%2024%20percentage%20point%20decline%20for%20the%20ST%20population%20in%20comparison%20to%20a%20decline%20of%209%20and%205%20percentage%20points%20for%20the%20Other%20Backward%20Caste%20and%20General%20categories%20respectively%2C%20the%20paper%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701502892000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F03%2Fopen-defecation-swachh-barat_flickr.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fworld-banks-research-paper-that-concluded-declining-trend-of-toilet-usage-in-india-withdr