20accused%20of%20planning%20the%20attack.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20incarcerated%20former%20gang%20member%20and%20one-time%20FBI%20informant%20was%20charged%20Friday%20with%20attempted%20murder%20in%20the%20stabbing%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fderek-chauvin-sentence-george-floyd-murder-2021-6%3F_gl%3D1*1ojfknx*_ga*MTcwOTQ2MzkuMTY5NTA2MzczNQ..*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTcwMTQ3MzM2OC4yMTQuMS4xNzAxNDc1MDI0LjM0LjAuMA..%5C%22%3Eex-Minneapolis%20police%20Officer%20Derek%20Chauvin%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20federal%20prison%20in%20Arizona.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Turscak%20stabbed%20Chauvin%2022%20times%20at%20the%20Federal%20Correctional%20Institution%20in%20Tucson%20and%20said%20he%20would%20have%20killed%20Chauvin%20had%20correctional%20officers%20not%20responded%20so%20quickly%2C%20federal%20prosecutors%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurscak%2C%20serving%20a%2030-year%20sentence%20for%20crimes%20committed%20while%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Mexican%20Mafia%20gang%2C%20told%20investigators%20he%20thought%20about%20attacking%20Chauvin%20for%20about%20a%20month%20because%20the%20former%20officer%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fminneapolis-businesses-shops-board-up-prepare-derek-chauvin-trial-2021-4%5C%22%3Econvicted%20of%20murdering%20George%20Floyd%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20a%20high-profile%20inmate%2C%20prosecutors%20said.%20Turscak%20later%20denied%20wanting%20to%20kill%20Chauvin%2C%20prosecutors%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurscak%20is%20accused%20of%20attacking%20Chauvin%20with%20an%20improvised%20knife%20in%20the%20prison's%20law%20library%20around%2012%3A30%20p.m.%20on%20Nov.%2024%2C%20the%20day%20after%20Thanksgiving.%20The%20Bureau%20of%20Prisons%20said%20employees%20stopped%20the%20attack%20and%20performed%20%26quot%3Blife-saving%20measures.%26quot%3B%20Chauvin%20was%20taken%20to%20a%20hospital%20for%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurscak%20told%20FBI%20agents%20interviewing%20him%20after%20the%20assault%20that%20he%20attacked%20Chauvin%20on%20Black%20Friday%20as%20a%20symbolic%20connection%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblack-lives-matter-history-social-media-movement-growth-2020-6%5C%22%3Ethe%20Black%20Lives%20Matter%20movement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20garnered%20widespread%20support%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgeorge-floyd-protests-defining-history-politics-election-black-lives-matter-2020-6%5C%22%3EFloyd's%20death%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20%26quot%3BBlack%20Hand%26quot%3B%20symbol%20associated%20with%20the%20Mexican%20Mafia%2C%20prosecutors%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurscak%2C%2052%2C%20is%20also%20charged%20with%20assault%20with%20intent%20to%20commit%20murder%2C%20assault%20with%20a%20dangerous%20weapon%2C%20and%20assault%20resulting%20in%20serious%20bodily%20injury.%20The%20attempted%20murder%20and%20assault%20with%20intent%20to%20commit%20murder%20charges%20are%20each%20punishable%20by%20up%20to%2020%20years%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20scheduled%20to%20complete%20his%20current%20sentence%20in%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lawyer%20for%20Turscak%20was%20not%20listed%20in%20court%20records.%20Turscak%20has%20represented%20himself%20from%20prison%20in%20numerous%20court%20matters.%20After%20the%20stabbing%2C%20he%20was%20moved%20to%20an%20adjacent%20federal%20penitentiary%20in%20Tucson%2C%20where%20he%20remained%20in%20custody%20on%20Friday%2C%20inmate%20records%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMessages%20seeking%20comment%20were%20left%20with%20Chauvin's%20lawyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChauvin%2C%2047%2C%20was%20sent%20to%20FCI%20Tucson%20from%20a%20maximum-security%20Minnesota%20state%20prison%20in%20August%202022%20to%20simultaneously%20serve%20a%2021-year%20federal%20sentence%20for%20violating%20Floyd's%20civil%20rights%20and%20a%2022%C2%BD-year%20state%20sentence%20for%20second-degree%20murder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChauvin's%20lawyer%20at%20the%20time%2C%20Eric%20Nelson%2C%20had%20advocated%20for%20keeping%20him%20out%20of%20the%20general%20population%20and%20away%20from%20other%20inmates%2C%20anticipating%20he%20would%20be%20a%20target.%20In%20Minnesota%2C%20Chauvin%20was%20mainly%20kept%20in%20solitary%20confinement%20%26quot%3Blargely%20for%20his%20own%20protection%2C%26quot%3B%20Nelson%20wrote%20in%20court%20papers%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFloyd%2C%20who%20was%20Black%2C%20died%20on%20May%2025%2C%202020%2C%20after%20Chauvin%2C%20who%20is%20white%2C%20pressed%20a%20knee%20on%20his%20neck%20for%209%C2%BD%20minutes%20on%20the%20street%20outside%20a%20convenience%20store%20where%20Floyd%20was%20suspected%20of%20trying%20to%20pass%20a%20counterfeit%20%2420%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBystander%20video%20captured%20Floyd's%20fading%20cries%20of%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20breathe.%26quot%3B%20His%20death%20touched%20off%20protests%20worldwide%2C%20some%20of%20which%20turned%20violent%2C%20and%20forced%20a%20national%20reckoning%20with%20police%20brutality%20and%20racism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurscak%20led%20a%20faction%20of%20the%20Mexican%20Mafia%20in%20the%20Los%20Angeles%20area%20in%20the%20late%201990s%2C%20going%20by%20the%20nickname%20%26quot%3BStranger%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20court%20records.%20He%20became%20an%20FBI%20informant%20in%201997%2C%20providing%20information%20about%20the%20gang%20and%20recordings%20of%20conversations%20he%20had%20with%20other%20Mexican%20Mafia%20members%20and%20associates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20investigation%20led%20to%20more%20than%2040%20indictments.%20But%20about%20midway%20through%2C%20the%20FBI%20dropped%20Turscak%20as%20an%20informant%20because%20he%20was%20still%20dealing%20drugs%2C%20extorting%20money%2C%20and%20authorizing%20assaults.%20According%20to%20court%20papers%2C%20Turscak%20plotted%20attacks%20on%20rival%20gang%20members%20and%20was%20accused%20of%20attempting%20to%20kill%20a%20leader%20of%20a%20rival%20Mexican%20Mafia%20faction%20while%20also%20being%20targeted%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurscak%20pleade