ills%20that%20they%20have%20previously%20withheld%20assent%20to%2C%20advising%C2%A0Tamil%20Nadu%20governor%20R.N.%20Ravi%20to%20resolve%20the%20impasse%20with%20the%20state%20government%20over%2010%20Bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Fjudiciary%2Fcant-withhold-assent-then-refer-to-president-sc-asks-tn-governor-to-resolve-impasse-over-bills%2F1867039%2F%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Print%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20three-judge%20bench%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20made%20the%20verbal%20suggestion%20to%20attorney%20general%20R.%20Venkataramani.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERavi%20had%20withheld%20assent%20to%2010%20Bills%2C%20that%20pertained%20to%20modifications%20in%20state%20university%20laws%2C%20which%20the%20legislature%20passed%20again%20without%20any%20amendments%20but%20later%20referred%20them%20to%20the%20President%2C%20just%20days%20after%20the%20top%20court%20questioned%20the%20governor%20for%20sitting%20on%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2013%2C%20the%20governor%20said%20he%20had%20withheld%20his%20assent%20to%20the%2010%20Bills%2C%20which%20also%20took%20away%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20powers%2C%20as%20chancellor%20of%20state%20universities%2C%20to%20appoint%20vice-chancellors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubsequently%2C%20the%20state%20assembly%20convened%20a%20special%20session%20on%20November%2018%20and%20passed%20them%20again.%20On%20November%2020%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20asked%20the%20governor%20about%20the%20pending%20Bills.%20On%20November%2028%2C%20the%20governor%20referred%20them%20to%20the%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Print%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20said%20on%20Friday%20that%20under%20Article%20200%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20the%20governor%20has%20only%20three%20options%20%E2%80%94%20grant%20assent%2C%20withhold%20assent%20or%20refer%20it%20to%20the%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20%E2%80%9Calternatives%E2%80%9D%20and%20once%20he%20has%20withheld%20assent%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20is%20no%20question%20of%20him%20referring%20them%20to%20the%20president%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20CJI%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20stressed%20once%20again%20that%20the%20proviso%20of%20Article%20200%20does%20not%20allow%20the%20governor%20to%20stall%20a%20Bill%20once%20it%20is%20re-enacted%20by%20the%20assembly.%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20referred%20to%20the%20top%20court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20on%20November%2010%20concerning%20the%20Punjab%20governor%E2%80%99s%20delay%C2%A0in%20assenting%20to%20certain%20Bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fsc-says-no-question-of-tamil-nadu-governor-referring-10-re-enacted-bills-to-president-now%2Farticle67593997.ece%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government%20told%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Friday%20that%20Ravi%20was%20exhibiting%20%E2%80%9Cconstitutional%20obstinacy%E2%80%9D%20by%20referring%20the%2010%20re-enacted%20Bills%20to%20the%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAG%C2%A0Venkataramani%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20argued%20that%20the%20governor%20had%20%E2%80%9Csimply%20withheld%20assent%E2%80%9D%20on%20November%2013%20and%20did%20not%20send%20them%20back.%20%E2%80%9CNow%2C%20this%20was%20not%20a%20case%20when%20the%20Governor%20had%20asked%20the%20Assembly%20to%20reconsider%20the%20Bills%20or%20had%20recommended%20changes.%20Here%2C%20he%20had%20only%20communicated%20to%20the%20Assembly%20on%20November%2013%20that%20he%20had%20withheld%20assent%E2%80%A6%20The%20Bills%20were%20not%20technically%20sent%20back%20to%20the%20Assembly%20for%20reconsideration%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20argued%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20you%20are%20saying%20the%20governor%20can%20just%20withhold%20consent%20and%20virtually%20kill%20the%20Bills%3F%E2%80%9D%20the%20CJI%20responded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20also%20asked%20the%20governor%20to%20engage%20with%20the%20chief%20minister.%20%E2%80%9CLet%20them%20sit%20down%20and%20discuss%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20AG%E2%80%99s%20response%20was%20%E2%80%9Cbleak%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20that%20there%20were%20cases%20when%20%E2%80%9Cboth%20do%20not%20have%20any%20bonhomie%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701450022000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F26113713%2FScreenshot-2022-04-26-at-11.37.07-AM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-tn-governor-10-bills-impasse%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22CJI%20Chandrachud%20said%20on%20Friday%20that%20under%20Article%20200%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20the%20governor%20has%20only%20three%20'alternatives'%20%E2%80%94%20grant%20assent%2C%20withhold%20assent%20or%20refer%20it%20to%20the%20president.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-tn-governor-10-bills-impasse%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Truce%20with%20Hamas%20has%20ended%20-%20what%20will%20Israel%20do%20now%3F%20%7C%20Sean%20Bell%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701449940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-gaza-israel-hamas_6379095.png%3F20231201193355%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fisrael-hamas-war-the-truce-has-ended-why-have-negotiations-stalled-and-what-will-israel-do-now-13020460%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Within%20half%20an%20hour%20of%20the%20latest%20truce%20ending%20on%20Friday%2C%20Israeli%20fighter%20jets%20were%20bombing%20Gaza%2C%20and%20Hamas%20was%20firing%20salvos%20of%20rockets%20into%20Israel.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fisrael-hamas-war-the-truce-has-ended-why-have-nego